==English==
{{wikipediapar|cirrus cloud}}

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪrəs|-ɪrəs]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

#{{meteorology}} A principal high-level cloud type composed of detached [[cirriform]] elements in the form of white, delicate filaments, of white (or mostly white) patches, or of narrow bands, found at an [[altitude]] of above 7000 metres.

